      "summary": "Sync loom 2.8.19 — 7 global rule extensions (post-release audit bundle from kailash-py round-9/10 codify). Keyspace version bump invalidation parity, multi-site kwarg plumbing, __all__ module-scope hygiene, cross-SDK structural API divergence disposition, phantom transitive deps, post-release reviewer audit gate, framework dispatch method drift (iterate-the-data). Plus 7 SDK pin bumps reflecting PyPI releases this session including kaizen-agents 0.9.3 finally on PyPI.",
      "changes": [
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/tenant-isolation.md — added §3a Keyspace Version Bumps Require Invalidation-Path Sweep. When CacheKeyGenerator bumps default keyspace (v1→v2 for BP-049), EVERY invalidator MUST be audited same PR; use version-wildcard (dataflow:v*:*) to sweep legacy+current. Origin: kailash-py PR #522/#529 (dataflow 2.0.11→2.0.12 fast-patch).",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/security.md — added § Multi-Site Kwarg Plumbing. When security-relevant kwarg (policy, tenant, clearance, audit-id) is plumbed through a helper, EVERY call site MUST update same PR; 'safe default' is by definition the insecure default. Origin: kailash-py PR #522/#529 BP-049 validate_model plumbing miss on DataFlowEngine.validate_record sibling.",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/orphan-detection.md — added Rule 6 Module-Scope Public Imports Appear In __all__. Eagerly-imported-but-absent-from-__all__ is BLOCKED. `from pkg import *` drops advertised API; doc generators, typing tools, linters read __all__ as canonical. Origin: kailash-py PR #523/#529 (kailash-ml 0.11.0→0.11.1 fast-patch — DeviceReport + 3 siblings eagerly imported, omitted from __all__).",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/cross-sdk-inspection.md — added §3a Structural API-Divergence Disposition. When sibling SDK reports bug at API surface this SDK doesn't expose (kailash-rs#424 execute_raw arity divergence), disposition MUST include (a) Tier 2 test through sibling binding path and (b) structural invariant test locking signature. Origin: kailash-py issue #525 / PR #528.",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/dependencies.md — added § Phantom Transitive Deps — Resolve Via Lockfile Upgrade, Not Local Caps. When pip check / cargo tree -d / npm ls reports conflict whose root is unused transitive, fix via lockfile upgrade (uv lock --upgrade-package X + uv sync / cargo update -p / npm update) NOT manifest cap. Origin: kailash-py PR #530 (google-generativeai phantom held protobuf, blocked kailash-align 0.3.2). NOTE: file is 319 lines, 19 over soft 300-line cc-artifacts guideline — deliberately retained at this length given comprehensive multi-ecosystem coverage; flag for review.",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/agents.md — added Quality Gates table row 'After release (post-merge audit)': RECOMMENDED reviewer run against MERGED release commit on main as follow-up. If CRIT/HIGH surfaces, patch same session as x.y.z+1. Origin: kailash-py round-9→round-10 pattern (pre-release gates clean; post-release reviewer found CRIT+HIGH+2 MED; fast-patched within 20min as dataflow 2.0.12 + ml 0.11.1).",
        "MODIFIED (global): rules/framework-first.md — added § Framework Version-Stable Integration — Drive The Data, Not The Dispatch. When integrating external framework lifecycle hooks, if both dispatch method and handler list/dict exposed, iterate the DATA structure (stable across versions); dispatch method names are subject to underscore-prefix transitions and removal. Origin: kailash-nexus 2.1.0→2.1.1 — shipped calling app.router.startup()/.shutdown() crashed uvicorn lifespan on FastAPI versions that exposed only _startup; fix iterates on_startup/on_shutdown lists directly (what FastAPI's _DefaultLifespan does internally).",
